# usta-cli rules

Read [`AGENTS.md`](mdc:AGENTS.md) for the full rule set. The highlights:

- The crate graph is the law: `usta-core` ← `usta-ports` ← `usta-app` ← `usta-adapters` ← binary.
- `usta-core` and `usta-ports` are I/O free. No `tokio`, no `reqwest`, no `git2`, no `std::fs`, no `std::process`.
- `usta-app` cannot import `usta-adapters`. Compiler enforces this.
- Concrete adapters are wired only in `crates/usta-cli/src/wiring.rs`.
- `extract` is deterministic. No network LLM calls anywhere in the crate graph.
- New behavior goes behind a new trait (OCP). Traits stay narrow (ISP, ≤ 5 methods).
- Library crates use `thiserror`. `anyhow` only in the binary.
- Conventional Commits required. `cargo fmt --check`, `cargo clippy -D warnings`, `cargo test` must pass.
- Don't propose anything from [`docs/NON_GOALS.md`](mdc:docs/NON_GOALS.md) without an ADR.
- Path traversal: never write outside the resolved output directory.
- Update [`PLAN.md`](mdc:PLAN.md) as phases progress.
